==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repletion
<hw>Re*ple"tion</hw> <pr>(r?-pl?"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>repletio</ets> a filling up: cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧pl⟦eacute⟧tion</ets>. See <er>Replete</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of being replete; superabundant
fullness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The tree had too much <qex>repletion</qex>, and was oppressed with
its own sap.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Repleccioun [overeating] ne made her never sick.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Fullness of blood;
plethora.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repletive</ent>⟦br⟧
